## 2.3 LiNKsites Overage and Capacity Policy (Final)

Core overage rates:

- Outbound transfer: $0.013 per GiB
- DB egress: $0.117 per GB
- DB database size: $0.1625 per GB-month
- DB storage size: $0.0273 per GB-month
- DB MAU metric where applicable: $0.004225 per MAU-month

Service overages:

- Premium automations: $0.010 per execution
- Premium AI responses: $0.008 per response
- Premium extra blog posts: $24 each
- Enterprise automations: $0.008 per execution
- Enterprise AI responses: $0.006 per response
- Enterprise extra blog posts: $20 each

Capacity event rule:

- CPU and RAM are not unit-metered overages on Droplets.
- If sustained resource pressure forces resizing or migration, LiNKsites may apply a capacity surcharge equal to incremental provider cost plus 30%, prorated from resize date until migration or normalization is completed.

## 3. Shared Credit Economy (LiNKautowork + LiNKskills)

## 3.1 Pricing Logic and Cost Basis

- One shared credit currency across LiNKautowork and LiNKskills.
- Internal COGS baseline: $0.012 per credit.
- Minimum gross margin policy: 80% floor across published bundles.
- Billing unit for each run:
- total credits = execution credits + tool credits
- tool credits convert direct provider costs (LLM/API/OCR/enrichment/etc.) into credits with reliability buffer

## 3.2 Final Credit Bundles and PAYG

- Standard bundle: 2,500 credits/month at $199.99
- Effective price: about $0.080/credit
- Gross margin: about 85.0%

- Premium bundle: 10,000 credits/month at $699.99
- Effective price: about $0.070/credit
- Gross margin: about 82.9%

- Enterprise bundle: 25,000 credits/month at $1,624.99
- Effective price: about $0.065/credit
- Gross margin: about 81.5%

- PAYG (no bundle): $0.10/credit
- Gross margin: about 88.0%

Overage credit rule:

- Bundle customers pay overage at their package-effective credit rate.
- Non-bundle customers pay PAYG rate.

## 3.3 Why This Model Was Chosen

- Keeps entry barrier low for light users.
- Preserves margins on heavy runs by passing variable tool costs through tool credits.
- Supports outcome-based billing rather than flat subscriptions.
- Creates one commercial model usable by both LiNKautowork and LiNKskills.

